<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <title>3RS</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/all.css">
</head>

<body>
    <%- include('partials/header') %>

        <div class="container">
            <header>
                <h1>What is 3 R's?</h1>
                <p>The concept of 3Rs for environmental protection refers to the three Rs: Reduce, Reuse, and Recycle.
                    These
                    three Rs aim to minimize waste, conserve natural resources, and reduce pollution. Reduce refers to
                    reducing waste and pollution, involving reducing the amount of waste generated, reusing, and
                    recycling
                    materials, and promoting sustainable practices. Reuse refers to reusing materials that can be
                    reused,
                    reducing the need for extracting, processing, and reusing materials. Recycle involves recycling
                    materials, reducing waste, and reusing materials that can be reused, reducing the need for
                    extracting,
                    processing, and reusing materials. These three Rs work together to minimize waste, conserve natural
                    resources, and reduce pollution.</p>
            </header>

            <!-- Principles Section -->
            <section class="principles">
                <h2>The concept of 3 R's following three basic principles</h2>
                <div class="principle-cards">
                    <div class="card">
                        <img src="/images/reduce-image.jpg" alt="Reduce image">
                        <h3>Reduce</h3>
                        <p>Reduce in the context of environmental protection refers to the practice of minimizing the
                            amount
                            of waste and pollution generated by human activities, thereby reducing the negative impact
                            on
                            the environment.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card">
                        <img src="/images/reuse-plastic.jpg" alt="Reuse image">
                        <h3>Reuse</h3>
                        <p>Reuse in the context of environmental protection refers to the practice of using an item
                            again
                            for its original purpose or for a new purpose, thereby reducing the need to extract,
                            process,
                            and transport raw materials to manufacture a new item.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card">
                        <img src="/images/recycle-image.jpg" alt="Recycle image">
                        <h3>Recycle</h3>
                        <p>Recycle in the context of environmental protection refers to the process of collecting and
                            processing materials that would otherwise be thrown away, and transforming them into new
                            products.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="importances">
                <h2>Importances of 3 R's</h2>
                <h4>Reduce:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Conserves natural resources by reducing the need to extract and process raw materials</li>
                    <li>Decreases the amount of waste generated, which in turn reduces the amount of waste sent to
                        landfills
                    </li>
                    <li>Helps to reduce pollution by decreasing the amount of energy required to produce new products
                    </li>
                    <li>Saves energy and water by reducing the need for production and processing</li>
                    <li>Reduces the need for new raw materials, which can help to preserve natural habitats and
                        ecosystems
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h4>Reuse:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Extends the life of products and materials, delaying the need for replacement</li>
                    <li>Reduces the need for single-use products, which can help to decrease litter and waste</li>
                    <li>Helps to preserve the embodied energy of products, which is the energy required to manufacture
                        and
                        transport them</li>
                    <li>Encourages creativity and innovation in finding new uses for existing materials</li>
                    <li>Can help to reduce the cost of production and consumption by reducing the need for new raw
                        materials
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <h4>Recycle:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Closes the loop on production and consumption, allowing materials to be continually cycled back
                        into
                        production</li>
                    <li>Helps to extract valuable materials from waste, reducing the need for virgin raw materials</li>
                    <li>Reduces the amount of waste sent to landfills, which in turn reduces the production of methane
                        and
                        other greenhouse gases</li>
                    <li>Creates a market for recyclable materials, which can help to stimulate economic growth and
                        create
                        jobs</li>
                    <li>Helps to conserve landfill space, which is a valuable resource in many urban areas</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="benefits">
                <h2>Benefits of 3 R's</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Reduces the financial costs associated with waste disposal and management</li>
                    <li>Helps to preserve biodiversity by reducing the impact of human activities on the environment
                    </li>
                    <li>Decreases the risk of pollution and environmental damage caused by waste and industrial
                        activities
                    </li>
                    <li>Encourages sustainable consumption and production patterns</li>
                    <li>Supports the development of a circular economy, where resources are used efficiently and waste
                        is
                        minimized</li>
                    <li>Helps to reduce the amount of litter and waste in public spaces, improving aesthetics and
                        quality of
                        life</li>
                    <li>Increases public awareness and education about environmental issues and the importance of
                        sustainability</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="how-to-start">
                <h2>How to Start Natural Farming</h2>
                <p style="font-size: 18px;">Starting 3 R's involves several methods:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Conduct a waste audit:</strong> Take a closer look at your daily habits and identify
                        areas
                        where you can reduce waste. Check your trash and recycling bins to see what types of waste
                        you're
                        generating.</li>
                    <li><strong>Choose products with minimal packaging:</strong> When shopping, opt for products with
                        minimal or biodegradable packaging.</li>
                    <li><strong>Avoid single-use items:</strong> Refuse single-use items like plastic bags, straws, and
                        water bottles. Instead, use reusable alternatives like cloth bags, metal straws, and refillable
                        water bottles.</li>
                    <li><strong>Use reusable containers:</strong> Use containers made of glass, stainless steel, or
                        ceramic
                        to store food and other items instead of disposable containers.</li>
                    <li><strong>Repurpose items:</strong> Get creative and find new uses for items you might otherwise
                        throw
                        away. For example, use old jars to store spices or turn an old t-shirt into a reusable bag.</li>
                    <li><strong>Use rags instead of paper towels:</strong> Use old clothes or towels to clean up spills
                        and
                        wipe down surfaces instead of paper towels.</li>
                    <li><strong>Learn what can be recycled:</strong> Check with your local recycling program to learn
                        what
                        materials are accepted.</li>
                    <li><strong>Set up a recycling system:</strong> Designate a bin or area for recyclables and make
                        sure
                        everyone in your household knows what can be recycled.</li>
                </ol>
            </section>

            <!-- Resources Section -->
            <section class="resources">
                <h2>Resources and Further Reading</h2>
                <p>For those interested in learning more about environmental protection, here are some recommended
                    resources:</p>
                <ul>
